        "marks": 1,
        "workedSolution": "Heat from the core, together with heat released by radioactive decay in the mantle, warms mantle material from below.\nHeated material expands, becomes less dense and rises; near the top it cools, becomes denser and sinks again. This circulating flow is a convection current, and the drag it exerts on the base of the plates helps to move them.\nSlab pull at subduction zones and ridge push are the other forces involved.",
