        "workedSolution": "As oceanic crust moves away from a ridge it cools, thickens and grows denser than the mantle beneath it.\nAt the trench this cold, dense edge sinks under gravity, and because the slab is attached to the rest of the plate, its descent pulls the plate along behind it.\nSlab pull is now regarded as one of the strongest forces driving plate motion.",
