        "workedSolution": "Where two oceanic plates converge, the older and denser plate subducts beneath the other.\nThe bending of the descending plate creates a deep ocean trench. As the slab descends, water driven from it lowers the melting point of the overlying mantle; magma rises and erupts on the seabed, building submarine volcanoes that grow into a curved chain of volcanic islands (an island arc).\nRidges and rift valleys form at divergent boundaries, and fold mountains require continental crust.",
        "misconceptionTag": "oceanic-oceanic-convergence",
