        "workedSolution": "The syllabus explains trade-offs as arising from two facts: resources (money, land, time, manpower) are limited, and different groups in society want different things.\nWhen both are true, a government cannot fully satisfy every group at once, so it must weigh priorities and give up some of one benefit to gain another.\nThe other options are neither necessary nor sufficient causes of a trade-off.",
