      "kind": "definition",
      "term": "Oxygen debt",
      "topic": "B6 Respiration in Humans",
      "body": "The extra oxygen a person must take in after vigorous exercise in order to break down the lactic acid that built up in the muscles during anaerobic respiration. It explains the deep, rapid breathing that continues after a race."
